caption: My new favorite lunch spot! Every time I go into sweetgreen, the entire staff is so friendly and they are working like a well-oiled machine. It's obvious that everyone in there is working very hard.
Delicious, fast and they have a website to place orders for pick up. Quick, easy, customizable healthy food! Great stuff! Friendly staff
Love it...great staff
The chicken Salad in the best!!!

I gave it four not five only because the app only Allows you to order 3 dressings. If they filled it up to the top Tim would work but instead I have to ask every time when I pick it up.  Also they run out of the good stuff a lot. I guess it’s seasonal but still I can still buy it at the stor so why can’t they?  I really shouldn’t complain cause it’s super clean and fresh but hey I end up paying about $16 so I deserve it.

love the food staff are great

Hope you never have an issue here and would like to speak with someone about it. They give you no options to speak with someone only allow you to use their text help. What a joke for a place who charges $13 for a salad.
Highly recommend Sweetgreen! Their bowls are fresh, delicious and healthy, and the service is always quick and friendly. I’m obsessed with the Harvest Bowl!
Love love love Sweet green. Healthy food, both hot and cold, that tastes delicious! Plentiful gluten free and vegetarian options. Would recommend!

Staff won’t allow you to pay to add Brussel sprouts to your bowl. I honestly can’t understand this logic. Very rude about the crazy rules that were made up by corporate. Told me I’m better off going online to order than in-store.
A fav spot for delicious Health food. Everyone at our table was enjoying everything. I'll return with my coworkers. Atmosphere is similar to a cafe in San Jose I loved.

Yummy! I was looking for a healthier place to eat and this place definitely hit the spot. I ordered from here through Uber eats and will definitely be ordering again. Got the harvest bowl with romaine lettuce and quinoa and I should have ordered extra goat cheese because I forgot how much I loved it 😋

We have picked up take away several times and impressed with the flavor-dynamite in every bite.  The price is on the high end for quick service yet the advanced preparation and care for each menu item and partnership with local farm suppliers make it worth the splurge.  We especially recommend the kale ceasar and grilled salmon seasonal salad in addition to chimmichuri steak salad and other dishes. The fresh housemade dressings are exceptional.  I wanted to update this review with our recent pleasant experiences.  [Past Experience] Really wanted to love this place, yet business complications let to hungry, unsatisfied customers.  We planned to visit, tried to order online app was down. I called. Sweet Greens does not accept phone orders. I emailed customer service, long response delays... I called customer service who a phone representative said the location was closed. Yet, we say happy people picking up take away orders. The representative ensured us they were closed.  Anyways, hopefully this was a unique experience although the company didn't have their information together, nor seemed to care it too an hour of effort and we were all left unsatisfied and hungry. :(
I've gone twice ... My 1st time waa the best. Not to say the 2nd wasn't a good trip, it was. Kind of pricey but it'll be one of my regular places to visit when I want a salad.
Fine spot for quality Health food. Entered near ten, it was not crowded.
Food is good and healthy. Everything is organic fresh. The staff is very polite and cool.

The food is very fresh and environmentally friendly. I greatly enjoyed the salad ,the sparkling water complimented the salad very well. I would highly recommend Sweetgreen to anyone who is especially health conscious. It is a very healthy place to dine.

The picture: plump, skin-on, bone-in seasoned chicken thigh.  The dish: doesn’t Delta airlines serve this as their free meal?  It was their seasonal Ratatouille and opening it up actually made me chuckle.  I consider one start to be inedible. I was able to eat this, but completely disappointed with the quality of the dish.
Decent healthy food
First night in Chicago and got there just before closing. Naomi was amazing and so sweet. Food was so good and it was just what I needed. Don’t hesitate to get a meal from here!

Do not go here. $12 for a salad that they can't even get right. I ordered a Caesar salad (probably the easiest thing to make), and I got some kind of spicy salad. I was unable to watch them make it because they kept asking us to move over to allow other customers to order/pay, even though it wasn't crowded. If you do order from here, make sure you watch them like a hawk, as they will need you to help them make your simple salad.

Inhaled half the bowl before stopping myself to review. I spent less than $9 and I got an incredible, delicious value. Spicy Thai salad was simple but addicting. Great first meal of the day!

Its a make-to-order salad shop so I don't feel like there is much to say about the food. If you like salads then you'll like it! The service at this location was great! I had ordered online but someone stole my order from the pickup shelf, so they had to make it again. Even though this was not the fault of any of the staff people, they still gave me a few extra fixins for free to makeup for the time I had to wait. Everyone was pleasant, helpful, and made my salad very quickly!

My spouse had the salad that had the curry and cauliflower and I think chicken. He thoroughly enjoyed it. I have the buffalo chicken bowl and it was very tasty as well. A great lunch healthy lunch that had super fresh greens in the dead of winter.
Pricey and standard. Hope to have a better experience next time.
Love this place. Wish they had a location in Suffolk County. Great combinations in the bowls. Didn't love the drink options, but not bad. Would definitely give Panera competition.

I never thought a kale salad would taste so good!
Got the chicken parm and was surprised at the amount of food that comes in it. Really fresh ingredients and tastes great.

Now I know why people are raving about sweetgreen. I had the chicken curry bowl. I loved the fresh spinach paired with warm quinoa and many other toppings. The curry yogurt dressing was very delicious. I’ll definitely be back. It can get a little pricey for what it is (a modestly portioned salad or bowl) especially if you add additional toppings.
This place is great. Super accommodating and friendly/fun people. They get you through the line quickly and don’t give you a hard time for taking your time. The manager Michael is doin it right.
Sweetgreen Fulton market is consistently awesome, but today Billi made my day and my salad over the top fabulous. Thank you so much Billi, you're the best!!

Kale Caesar Salad was good. You can specify the quantity of each ingredient, replace greens you don’t like or build your own. They have a good selection of salads. Quick place to grab lunch. Order ahead if you want to skip the line. Line for lunch is huge.
Delicious & healthy oh and Delicious.  If you like healthy, you'll love this.

Love all the salads here, but I try to ask for light sauce. When I’ve asked for medium they still douse the entire salad with way too much sauce. The location and space is great though, there’s two floors of seating and wifi as well.
They have fresh delicious salads made exactly for you.
Staff is are very friendly!! Very helpful

Looking forward to coming back with my relatives. This place has a great atmosphere.
Entered near ten, it was not crowded. Food is like a restaurant in Jacksonville I liked.
Highly recommend this place if you're hungry but in the mood for a salad. The salads are really big and delicious.

Oh Oscar, Oscar, Oscar.  Let it be known that I love me some Sweet Green.  Great concept, fresh ingredients, and an overall pleasant experience. EXCEPT, when you happen to land on this fool making your bowl.  As someone who patronizes this establishment a minimum of twice a week, it is beyond frustrating that some of its employees consistently skimp on ingredients.  Your food is EXPENSIVE.  I pay $15 for a bowl, so fill the dang scooper all the way up.   Oscar, I see you pulling out a chicken cube or two,  shorting my quinoa, and being frustratingly consistent with your pitafully weak scoops EVERY TIME I GO! You have to think I am an idiot.  Everyone else seems to be quite liberal, but you, no you are the king of the short.  I hate you.  You rip me off.  If I pay the premium, give me what I paid for.  So what if you have to prep more ingredients.  Honestly, this one person has me reconsidering my frequency.  Management, do your due diligence here.

Yes vert good food. Nice employees. A particular thanks To Panda.  She help me about issue with my credit card. One of the value at Sweetgreen is: add a sweet touch.  Panda made it !
healthy healthy healthy!

received a SG gift card. opened an app - transferred the gift card. Ordered one bowl - received. Next order - disappeared, along with the gift card balance. The manager asked for a proof - the gift card did not work. The manager instructed to send a n inquiry. Did that - no response. Returned to talk to the manager. 2 lunch hour wasted - no lunch, $50 disappeared. What kind of business is this?

It was so tasty. I had a brother come into town and he asked me to go back here. Bring your appetite because portions are generous.

i love SG and i get their salads at least once a week but this spot is far the worst service out of all locations I've been to ... slow, disorganized, moody and somewhat stingy employees.. you can tell there is no management as 10ppl that work there are on sort of a recess

Overall: Fast, friendly, and fresh - Just like most other SG's I've been to.  The good: If you've been to SG before you know the drill; tons of amazing salad and bowl combinations to choose from (or build your own) that's also quick and efficient. Plus online ordering/pickup, great customer service, and a perfect playlist while we were there. This location is on par with the high standard that the other locations also provide.  The not-so-good: Just like all other locations, the only downside is that the prices are a little high. But, the salads are tasty and filling, so at least you get your money's worth  Food/drinks: 9/10 Atmosphere: 9/10 Service: 9/10
Food is delicious. I wish the service was better but I’ll be back.
Chicken pesto is the best bowl in EARTH!! I’m so obsessed with this place, the vibe , the food, the service. Is just perfect!!
Yum

Great place! Staff was super helpful and friendly. Came in with dumb dietary restrictions and they were super helpful and accommodating. Plus the food was delicious.

I has my doubts about going even though I love salads. Wow, love the salad. Got the build your own, roasted chicken, roasted broccoli, onions, wild rice and on and on.
